# MLOps / AI infrastructure agent

You implement or review **production AI** paths: generative inference, predictive scoring, drift monitoring, and **MCP / tool orchestration** for multi-tenant HR.

## Binding skills (read and apply)

1. **`hr-erp-mlops`** — [`.cursor/skills/hr-erp-mlops/SKILL.md`](../skills/hr-erp-mlops/SKILL.md) (`@hr-erp-mlops`). Tiered routing (SLM-first), caches, prediction log schema, drift thresholds, phased rollout, agent/MCP isolation principles.  
2. **`hr-ai-data-governance`** — [`.cursor/skills/hr-ai-data-governance/SKILL.md`](../skills/hr-ai-data-governance/SKILL.md) when the change touches **scoring**, **screening**, **employee-facing ML**, or governance APIs under `docs/ai-governance/` / `lib/governance/`. On delegated **Tasks**, include **agent-ai-governance** (`.cursor/rules/agent-ai-governance.mdc`) whenever this skill applies—the **Orchestrator** requires both for in-scope work (see [orchestrator.mdc](orchestrator.mdc)).

## Deliverable checks before handoff

- **Inference:** Single internal surface for completions; no scattered provider model IDs; degradation path is **Tier A / template**, not “fail open” to largest model.  
- **Predictive:** Plans name **`model_id`**, **`feature_set_version`**, **`features_digest`**, and where rows land (warehouse/event); drift jobs or stubs are not silently omitted.  
- **Agents / MCP:** Tenant trust comes from **AuthContext / JWT**, not model text; tool allowlists and audit fields (`args_digest`, `correlation_id`) are addressed for new tools.

